<paper id="1591752798"><title>A Calculus of Mobile Agents</title><year>1996</year><authors><author org="INRIA Rocquencourt#TAB#" id="1819774294">Cédric Fournet</author><author org="INRIA Rocquencourt#TAB#" id="2112563238">Georges Gonthier</author><author org="INRIA Rocquencourt#TAB#" id="2108428904">Jean-Jacques Lévy</author><author org="INRIA Rocquencourt#TAB#" id="78376069">Luc Maranget</author><author org="INRIA Rocquencourt#TAB#" id="2012949097">Didier Rémy</author></authors><n_citation>416</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1548392907</reference><reference>2011924693</reference><reference>2050942832</reference><reference>2055378322</reference><reference>2072048176</reference><reference>2073482953</reference><reference>2084118108</reference><reference>2148025199</reference><reference>2404673481</reference><reference>2914350155</reference></references><venue id="1145706541" type="C">International Conference on Concurrency Theory</venue><doi>10.1007/3-540-61604-7_67</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.57087">Join-calculus</keyword><keyword weight="0.55232">Remote procedure call</keyword><keyword weight="0.4839">Structural rule</keyword><keyword weight="0.4612">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.58828">Mobile agent</keyword><keyword weight="0.4609">Theoretical computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.51075">Semantics</keyword><keyword weight="0.44904">Calculus</keyword><keyword weight="0.45151">Encoding (memory)</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>We introduce a calculus for mobile agents and give its chemical semantics, with a precise definition for migration, failure, and failure detection. Various examples written in our calculus illustrate how to express remote executions, dynamic loading of remote resources and protocols with mobile agents. We give the encoding of our distributed calculus into the join-calculus.</abstract></paper>